-- Lesiak Hired at Canaccord, Markus Kiraly Joins TD, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-08-09T20:56:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-09/lesiak-hired-at-canaccord-markus-kiraly-joins-td-vlaad-says.html
Tony Lesiak rejoined Canaccord
Genuity as managing director and head of Canadian mining
research from Macquarie  Capital Markets , according to Vlaad &
Co., a Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Toronto-Dominion Bank hired Markus Kiraly from Bank of America
Corp. as head of global  emerging markets  foreign-exchange
trading at its TD Securities unit.  * Manulife Financial Inc. named Michael Huddart executive vice
president and general manager of operations in China, Hong Kong,
and Taiwan.  * Zach Blumer joined Morgan Bay Capital as an investment
analyst.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
